Google Ads API Tool Design Document
Lux Neon Art Gallery / Good Neon
March 2026

1. OVERVIEW
-----------
We are building an internal API integration to manage Google Ads campaigns for our own e-commerce businesses:
- Lux Neon Art Gallery (luxneonartgallery.com) — Shopify store
- Good Neon (goodneon.com) — WooCommerce store

The tool is used exclusively by our internal team (no external users or clients).

2. ARCHITECTURE
---------------
- Platform: Python-based automation scripts running on a secured internal server
- Authentication: OAuth 2.0 with offline refresh tokens
- API Version: Google Ads API v18/v19 (REST)
- Manager Account: 543-649-2290 (lux neon)
- Client Account: 933-885-5200 (Good Neon)

3. USE CASES
------------
3.1 Campaign Management
    - Create and modify Search campaigns targeting neon sign keywords
    - Create and modify Performance Max campaigns for Shopping
    - Adjust budgets and bidding strategies based on ROAS targets
    - Pause/enable campaigns and ad groups

3.2 Reporting & Analytics
    - Pull daily/weekly campaign performance metrics (impressions, clicks, conversions, spend, ROAS)
    - Generate keyword performance reports
    - Monitor search term reports for negative keyword optimization
    - Cross-reference Google Ads data with Google Analytics 4 (GA4) data

3.3 Product Feed Sync
    - Coordinate product catalog between Shopify/WooCommerce and Google Merchant Center
    - Ensure product data consistency across advertising channels
    - Monitor product disapprovals and feed health

3.4 Bid Optimization
    - Automated bid adjustments based on conversion data
    - Geographic bid modifiers for South Florida market focus
    - Device and time-of-day bid adjustments

4. DATA FLOW
------------
[Internal Server] → Google Ads API (REST/v18)
                  → Campaign CRUD operations
                  → Performance data retrieval
                  → Budget management
                  
[Google Merchant Center] ← Product feed (automated via WooCommerce/Shopify plugins)
                        → Shopping campaigns in Google Ads

5. RATE LIMITING & COMPLIANCE
-----------------------------
- All API calls respect Google Ads API rate limits
- No automated account creation
- No bulk account management (own accounts only)
- Developer token used solely for our own advertising accounts
- All API usage complies with Google Ads API Terms & Conditions

6. SECURITY
-----------
- OAuth credentials stored in encrypted environment files
- Refresh tokens never exposed in logs or UI
- API access limited to authorized internal team members
- No customer PII is transmitted through the API

7. TEAM
-------
- Tool Developer: Internal team (Jackie AI Assistant)
- Account Owner: Nicolas Gonzalez (Lux Neon Art Gallery LLC)
